{"questionId":"30226734","questionHtml":"<p>Show that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi></math> is also a root (seen anywhere)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>recognition of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn></math> roots and attempt to sum these roots&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>p</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>7</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>p</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>7</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>11</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"30226734","referenceCode":"24M.1.AHL.TZ2.7b","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Show that p=1.","paper":"1","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","AHL 2.12—Factor and remainder theorems, sum and product of roots","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.12—Complex numbers – Cartesian form and Argand diag"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}